                            <comment id="12614182" author="jimk" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 01:19:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Why can&apos;t we do this? Is it a shell problem or a HBase region server problem or what?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614184" author="stack" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 01:22:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A rule on regionserver side IIRC&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614193" author="jimk" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 01:41:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Only the &lt;del&gt;ROOT&lt;/del&gt; table cannot be disabled. IMO, if the root table needs to be modified, it should be done off-line.&lt;br/&gt;
However, I see no restrictions on offlining the .META. table&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614194" author="stack" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 01:54:31 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Try the shell.  Will throw an exception.  Will help figure where the problem if any is.  Run &apos;disable &quot;.META.&quot;&apos;.  Maybe its a non-issue now?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12614491" author="jimk" created="Thu, 17 Jul 2008 18:55:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Removed client side checks and fixed bug in master. Committed.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
